item.description:

else if (command.equalsIgnoreCase("CommandName")) if(LogoutDelay == 0) { teleportToX = Xcoord; teleportToY = Ycoord; } if(LogoutDelay > 0){ sendMessage("You are in combat and can not be teleported at the moment."); }

Breaking it down:

if(LogoutDelay == 0) {

If you are in combat this tells the server that you will not be able to perform that function until out of combat.

if(LogoutDelay > 0){

This tells the server that the person is out of combat and the function can be performed.
